Back to the main point of your Question, which seems to ask how to interrupt the sibling tasks if one of those tasks encounters a specific situation. 

In Java, threads are interrupted cooperatively. You *could* ask the executor service to shutdown early, and it would try to interrupt each of its task’s threads. But interrupt handling is a bit tricky. I would suggest your set up a specific flag for all your tasks to share. This flag must be thread-safe. So I would use `AtomicBoolean` as a flag among your tasks that all is well and they should continue their work. Let&#39;s initialize that flag, and pass it as an argument when constructing our task objects.


