The `.group` method was removed in version 1.19.3

To add your item to an item group, you must use the `ItemGroupEvents.modifyEntriesEvent(ItemGroup group)` event provided by Fabric API.

In your case, you&#39;ll need to store the result of the `Registry.register` method in the `CUSTOM_ITEM` field if you want to pass it to the `modifyEntries` event:

```java
public static final Item CUSTOM_ITEM = Registry.register(Registry.ITEM, new Identifier(&quot;tutorial&quot;, &quot;custom_item&quot;), new Item(new FabricItemSettings()));

public void onInitialize() {
   ItemGroupEvents.modifyEntriesEvent(ItemGroup.MISC).register(itemGroup -&gt; 
   {
      // Add the custom item to the MISC item group.
      itemGroup.add(CUSTOM_ITEM);
   });
}
```

----------

You can read more about creating custom items here:

- https://fabric.mineblock11.dev/items/creating-first-item
- https://fabricmc.net/wiki/tutorial:items

